- run composer install
- maybe composer  dump-autoload
- edit config class
- edit db credentials in config class

Run tests with code coverage
./vendor/bin/phpunit --coverage-html ./report


!!The content type of POST request are application/x-www-form-urlencoded Content-Type

#REQUESTS
uri: /api/monsters
method: POST
description: Create new monster. 
Parameters: race, level, attack, defense, turns, isAlive, gold
response example:
{
    "id": "6",
    "race": "human",
    "gold": "5000",
    "level": "6",
    "attack": "46",
    "defense": "30",
    "turns": "10",
    "isAlive": true
}
Response will be a monster resource object with all its attributes.


uri: /api/monsters/
method: GET
description:Get all monsters from database
response example:

[
    {
        "id": "1",
        "race": "human",
        "gold": "50",
        "level": "1",
        "attack": "100",
        "defense": "200",
        "turns": "2000",
        "isAlive": true
    },
    {
        "id": "2",
        "race": "elf",
        "gold": "40",
        "level": "3",
        "attack": "100",
        "defense": "250",
        "turns": "10",
        "isAlive": true
    }
]
If no monster is found status code will be 404 and response will be an empty array


uri: /api/monsters/144
method: GET
description: Get a monster by id
response example:

{
    "id": "5",
    "race": "elf",
    "gold": "5000",
    "level": "5",
    "attack": "46",
    "defense": "30",
    "turns": "10",
    "isAlive": true
}
If no monster is found status code will be 404 and all fields will have null value.

PUT - update if exists, error if not
DELETE - delete by id

